snippet.textDisplay: I listened to this album for the first time when I did molly for the first time. It brought full on tears of melancholic joy to my face and I had the thought “this is the last first time I will listen to a Mac Miller album.” I was so happy to hear his voice again and so sad that he’s gone. This album will forever hold a special place in my heart. Most people might not agree but this is the first album since Pink Floyd’s Dark Side of the Moon where there wasn’t a single track that I disliked. Hold on to the little stuff everyone because we’re in the good old days right now.

snippet.textDisplay:
Man... Sometimes Anthony confuses the absolute Hell outta me.
I love Mac's earlier stuff, don't get me wrong. But from 'GO:OD AM' thenceforth, his sound was f***ing FIRE! You could hear the maturity settling in quite comfortably in songs like 'Favorite Part', and 'Small Worlds'. The absolute poeticism and R&B production - for someone like Anthony, I woulda thought... What's not to like?
I'm beyond ecstatic that he loves the album, yes. But hell... It's miraculous compared to what you thought about the rest of his layer stuff.
